WEBVTT

1
00:00:40.040 --> 00:00:42.750
<i>Man. thought you'd be
off the clock by five.</i>

2
00:00:42.830 --> 00:00:45.710
<i>they keep you on call. Shitluck.</i>

3
00:00:46.300 --> 00:00:48.110
<i>Cap said I could leave
my gun and badge</i>

4
00:00:48.130 --> 00:00:50.050
<i>if I went home to listen to my old lady</i>

5
00:00:50.130 --> 00:00:55.100
<i>go on and on about her online shopping
or whatever the hell she did all day.</i>

6
00:00:55.180 --> 00:00:57.970
<i>That's what you get
for choosing the life of a public servant.</i>

7
00:00:58.060 --> 00:01:00.440
<i>It just had to fucking rain.</i>

8
00:01:00.520 --> 00:01:03.100
Hmm? What the hell you doin'? Back it up.

9
00:01:03.190 --> 00:01:04.270
Looking to get shot?

10
00:01:30.880 --> 00:01:33.180
Got us a cyber psycho!

11
00:01:33.840 --> 00:01:35.680
Raise MaxTac now!

12
00:02:31.190 --> 00:02:32.860
We need to fry the system fast.

13
00:02:32.940 --> 00:02:35.110
Freak's supporting military-grade ICE!

14
00:02:35.200 --> 00:02:37.820
Meaning that our tech isn't? Get to it!

15
00:03:20.910 --> 00:03:22.290
<i>So. what do you think?</i>

16
00:03:22.910 --> 00:03:25.290
<i>Still warm. that. Couple hours old.</i>

17
00:03:25.370 --> 00:03:27.500
<i>Lifted from the edgerunner
who scrolled it.</i>

18
00:03:27.580 --> 00:03:29.250
<i>Straight off the street.</i>

19
00:03:29.330 --> 00:03:30.750
So. what!

20
00:03:30.840 --> 00:03:34.130
Doc. hey. you gotta tell me
who keeps feeding you these nuggets.

21
00:03:34.210 --> 00:03:35.590
<i>Kurosaki. Who else?</i>

22
00:03:35.670 --> 00:03:38.760
<i>Ain't no other editor who churns out
BDs that sweet and preem.</i>

23
00:03:38.840 --> 00:03:41.100
<i>Won't pull nothin' like that
off the shelf. neither.</i>

24
00:03:41.180 --> 00:03:44.270
No shit. Brain's still buzzing.
Gonna be sick.

25
00:03:44.350 --> 00:03:46.350
<i>Slow. deep breaths. choom.</i>

26
00:03:46.430 --> 00:03:49.100
<i>Just left the head
of a skezzed-out chrome junkie.</i>

27
00:03:49.190 --> 00:03:51.110
<i>Cyberpsychosis ain't no joke.</i>

28
00:03:51.190 --> 00:03:54.320
<i>Anyway. either hurl or don't.
got more chips for you to slot.</i>

29
00:03:54.400 --> 00:03:55.780
Really? What?

30
00:03:55.860 --> 00:03:58.030
<i>Something special.</i>

31
00:03:59.280 --> 00:04:01.780
Huh? Cut the shit. man!

32
00:04:15.550 --> 00:04:18.380
<i>Cycle suspended
due to insufficient funds.</i>

33
00:04:18.470 --> 00:04:21.470
- Geez. not again.
<i>- Cycle suspended due to in...</i>

34
00:04:21.550 --> 00:04:23.810
<i>It was a tragic scene
in Westbrook today</i>

35
00:04:23.890 --> 00:04:24.970
<i>when a corporate convoy</i>

36
00:04:25.060 --> 00:04:27.850
<i>- was ambushed by 6th Street...</i>
- God. Mom.

37
00:04:30.270 --> 00:04:31.270
Morning. Miho.

38
00:04:31.310 --> 00:04:33.060
If you keep sleeping on the couch.

39
00:04:33.150 --> 00:04:35.020
gonna get early onset arthritis.

40
00:04:35.110 --> 00:04:37.860
I know. Just dead
after my night shift. is all.

41
00:04:37.940 --> 00:04:41.240
You and the washing machine both.
Forget to re-up it?

42
00:04:41.320 --> 00:04:42.870
Yeah.

43
00:04:42.950 --> 00:04:44.830
I'll take care of it later. 'kay?

44
00:04:44.910 --> 00:04:48.120
Oh. money. right.
You mentioned a reef update for class.

45
00:04:48.200 --> 00:04:50.080
That happen yet?
When did you say you need it?

46
00:04:50.160 --> 00:04:54.000
No. no. It's fine. Got Doc to handle it.

47
00:04:54.840 --> 00:04:58.130
- What do you mean "handle it"?
- I'm good. All set.

48
00:04:58.210 --> 00:05:00.300
Don't go cutting corners. D.

49
00:05:00.380 --> 00:05:04.390
Already cashed my paycheck.
You'll get it updated right. Hear me?

50
00:05:04.470 --> 00:05:07.310
Mom. seriously!
Just feed the washer. alright?

51
00:05:07.390 --> 00:05:09.770
I forgot this time. I told you.

52
00:05:10.640 --> 00:05:12.480
Promise me you'll buy the update.

53
00:05:12.560 --> 00:05:14.400
Okay. okay.

54
00:05:14.480 --> 00:05:17.320
And you're really going to school
dressed like that?

55
00:05:17.400 --> 00:05:18.570
Uniform's soaked.

56
00:05:18.650 --> 00:05:20.130
<i>A military-grade implant...</i>

57
00:05:20.150 --> 00:05:21.460
<i>- ...was found missing from the body</i>
- Hmm?

58
00:05:21.490 --> 00:05:24.410
<i>of Lt. Col. James Norris.
shot dead by MaxTac...</i>

59
00:05:24.490 --> 00:05:27.790
Mom. you're on TV! Nova!

60
00:05:27.870 --> 00:05:30.660
Not Nova. David. A bloodbath.

61
00:05:30.750 --> 00:05:34.000
- Go on. Off to school.
- Bye.

62
00:05:34.080 --> 00:05:35.630
Love you. Miho.

63
00:05:40.720 --> 00:05:43.430
<i>Maine? It's Gloria.</i>

64
00:05:58.860 --> 00:06:00.530
<i>♪ I ain't your average sicko ♪</i>

65
00:06:00.610 --> 00:06:02.280
<i>♪ I'm dead. just like disco ♪</i>

66
00:06:02.360 --> 00:06:05.740
<i>♪ My bank account
Is zero-zero-zero. oh no ♪</i>

67
00:06:05.820 --> 00:06:07.870
<i>♪ I think I need a hero ♪</i>

68
00:06:07.950 --> 00:06:09.450
<i>♪ I don't have no ego ♪</i>

69
00:06:09.540 --> 00:06:11.620
<i>♪ 'Cause I'm spinnin' out now ♪</i>

70
00:06:19.710 --> 00:06:23.130
<i>♪ And now I'm getting older
My heart is growing colder ♪</i>

71
00:06:23.220 --> 00:06:25.970
<i>♪ Oh. that's fine ♪</i>

72
00:06:31.020 --> 00:06:34.270
<i>Trauma Team.
Clear a path immediately.</i>

73
00:06:34.850 --> 00:06:38.110
<i>Emergency evac underway. Emergency evac.</i>

74
00:06:38.190 --> 00:06:40.860
<i>All AVs. vacate the airway.</i>

75
00:06:40.940 --> 00:06:45.280
<i>Trauma Team. Clear a path immediately.
Trauma Team. Clear a path.</i>

76
00:06:45.360 --> 00:06:46.530
<i>Don't walk.</i>

77
00:06:48.200 --> 00:06:49.280
<i>Don't walk.</i>

78
00:06:50.950 --> 00:06:55.040
<i>Walk. Walk. Walk.</i>

79
00:06:55.120 --> 00:06:57.540
<i>Walk. Walk.</i>

80
00:07:01.380 --> 00:07:04.670
<i>♪ And now I'm getting older
My heart is growing colder ♪</i>

81
00:07:04.760 --> 00:07:07.680
<i>♪ Oh. that's fine ♪</i>

82
00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:14.180
<i>♪ I was a teenage outlaw
With no worries on my mind ♪</i>

83
00:07:15.350 --> 00:07:18.560
<i>♪ And now I'm getting older
My heart is growing colder ♪</i>

84
00:07:18.650 --> 00:07:20.440
<i>♪ Oh. that's fine ♪</i>

85
00:07:28.700 --> 00:07:32.080
<i>♪ You say it's over ♪</i>

86
00:08:00.860 --> 00:08:02.770
Good morning to you. class.

87
00:08:02.860 --> 00:08:05.780
Today's attendance. Zero absences.

88
00:08:05.860 --> 00:08:07.450
Martinez. David.

89
00:08:07.530 --> 00:08:10.110
You are not in compliance
with the Academy's dress code.

90
00:08:10.200 --> 00:08:12.120
Yeah. Real sorry about that.

91
00:08:12.200 --> 00:08:14.290
Afraid my uniform's still
at the cleaner's.

92
00:08:14.370 --> 00:08:16.390
Do you have a spare uniform?

93
00:08:16.410 --> 00:08:17.870
Yeah. Spare's there too.

94
00:08:17.960 --> 00:08:21.960
Understood. Please submit
a Uniform Exception form after class.

95
00:08:22.040 --> 00:08:24.300
Now. let us begin today's lesson.

96
00:08:24.380 --> 00:08:27.840
- You will observe...
<i>- Gutter rat. Rat off the street.</i>

97
00:08:27.920 --> 00:08:30.430
<i>Me? Nah. Wouldn't show my face.</i>

98
00:08:30.510 --> 00:08:34.100
<i>Cray-crazy. I know.
but some of us here to learn to learn.</i>

99
00:08:34.180 --> 00:08:35.970
<i>With that fossiltech?</i>

100
00:08:36.060 --> 00:08:38.560
<i>Updates. man. Bet it's not compatible.</i>

101
00:08:38.640 --> 00:08:40.560
<i>I made it compatible.</i>

102
00:08:40.650 --> 00:08:42.480
<i>Huh? How?</i>

103
00:08:42.560 --> 00:08:44.070
<i>How I had to.</i>

104
00:08:44.150 --> 00:08:45.780
<i>Life's gotta be gotta be shit</i>

105
00:08:45.860 --> 00:08:48.320
<i>when a two-bit wreath
costs your life savings.</i>

106
00:08:48.400 --> 00:08:49.240
At this time.

107
00:08:49.320 --> 00:08:52.740
I ask all students
to log into the Green Room for meditation.

108
00:08:52.820 --> 00:08:54.330
Countin' on ya. Doc.

109
00:08:59.160 --> 00:09:00.580
<i>- Seriously?</i>
- What?

110
00:09:00.670 --> 00:09:02.430
<i>Martinez again!</i>

111
00:09:02.460 --> 00:09:05.840
<i>Not again!</i>

112
00:09:08.840 --> 00:09:11.930
I'm so sorry
for the inconvenience my son has caused.

113
00:09:12.010 --> 00:09:15.300
I wouldn't call this
a matter of money. Mrs. Martinez.

114
00:09:15.390 --> 00:09:19.430
Although I must say it was quite
an expense for us to restore the system.

115
00:09:19.520 --> 00:09:22.230
Of course.
and I will pay for the repairs.

116
00:09:23.230 --> 00:09:26.860
As I understand it.
Mr. Martinez modified his headset

117
00:09:26.940 --> 00:09:30.900
with backalley software
to avoid paying for the licensed update.

118
00:09:30.990 --> 00:09:34.740
This is not behavior befitting a pupil
from a financially stable home.

119
00:09:34.820 --> 00:09:37.870
It's not a problem. really.
We can afford it.

120
00:09:37.950 --> 00:09:39.150
Be that as it may.

121
00:09:39.200 --> 00:09:41.960
I see an opportunity here
to improve David's situation.

122
00:09:42.040 --> 00:09:43.180
Meaning what. exactly?

123
00:09:43.210 --> 00:09:46.090
David is not a good fit
with his classmates.

124
00:09:47.090 --> 00:09:49.510
He could benefit
from a change in environment.

125
00:09:49.590 --> 00:09:52.720
No! Wait. please.
I mean. he has to stay here.

126
00:09:52.800 --> 00:09:56.260
He deserves this education as much
as every other child in this school.

127
00:09:56.350 --> 00:09:59.100
What happened?
Didn't I tell you to get the upgrade?

128
00:09:59.180 --> 00:10:02.310
Yeah. Doc's damn fault.
Gave me a faulty port drive.

129
00:10:02.390 --> 00:10:04.900
You tried to get around
the system. didn't you?

130
00:10:04.980 --> 00:10:07.320
Now. it'll cost us ten times more.

131
00:10:07.400 --> 00:10:08.730
Sorry.

132
00:10:08.820 --> 00:10:10.420
If it's something
you gotta apologize for.

133
00:10:10.440 --> 00:10:12.450
maybe don't do it in the first place. hey?

134
00:10:12.530 --> 00:10:15.010
You said you didn't have
the eddies when I asked. so...

135
00:10:15.030 --> 00:10:16.780
I was waiting for payday!

136
00:10:16.870 --> 00:10:19.950
You know we don't got that kind of cash
just lying around.

137
00:10:20.040 --> 00:10:23.000
Can't you sit still a minute?

138
00:10:25.290 --> 00:10:28.040
You know.
I've been thinkin' lately.

139
00:10:28.130 --> 00:10:29.550
About what?

140
00:10:29.630 --> 00:10:33.170
Maybe I drop out.
Find some work or whatever.

141
00:10:33.260 --> 00:10:34.840
Do you hear yourself?

142
00:10:34.930 --> 00:10:37.890
C'mon. seriously.
You know we can't afford those repairs.

143
00:10:38.970 --> 00:10:43.680
Plus. you got no idea just how bad
I stand out compared to all of them.

144
00:10:43.770 --> 00:10:47.360
Anyone sides a true blue corpo
gets shit on.

145
00:10:47.440 --> 00:10:49.360
Even if I do graduate.
they'll never accept me.

146
00:10:49.440 --> 00:10:51.980
No kid from Santo will ever be a suit.

147
00:10:52.070 --> 00:10:53.990
I don't wanna be one anyway.

148
00:10:57.660 --> 00:10:58.780
So. you tell me.

149
00:10:58.870 --> 00:11:01.410
What have I been busting
my ass for then. huh?

150
00:11:02.080 --> 00:11:05.460
Everything I do. I do for you. D.

151
00:11:05.540 --> 00:11:06.830
Don't you see that?

152
00:11:06.920 --> 00:11:11.050
You're breaking my heart. Miho.

153
00:11:11.130 --> 00:11:12.130
Wait. What?

154
00:11:12.210 --> 00:11:16.800
My sweet baby boy. So smart. so talented.

155
00:11:16.880 --> 00:11:18.140
You're everything to me.

156
00:11:18.220 --> 00:11:22.060
I want to give you a fighting chance
in this city and a good education.

157
00:11:22.140 --> 00:11:26.940
It's why I put in all of those hours.
Why I'm never home.

158
00:11:29.060 --> 00:11:30.610
Uh. I'm sorry.

159
00:11:31.230 --> 00:11:35.030
Shouldn't have brought it up.
Don't cry. Mom.

160
00:11:35.110 --> 00:11:37.740
Think I don't know
how they treat you?

161
00:11:37.820 --> 00:11:39.740
Think I don't get treated the same way?

162
00:11:41.030 --> 00:11:43.580
But that's why you gotta prove them wrong.

163
00:11:43.660 --> 00:11:45.910
You have to work hard
and rise through the ranks.

164
00:11:46.000 --> 00:11:50.040
My son at Arasaka Tower top floor!
I can just see it.

165
00:11:50.130 --> 00:11:52.590
You've got this. D. You're my son.

166
00:11:53.170 --> 00:11:54.880
Yeah. well. easier said than done.

167
00:12:00.090 --> 00:12:02.850
Fuck 'em up!

168
00:12:05.390 --> 00:12:08.640
- Don't let 'em get away!
- Suit's limo's titanium plated!

169
00:12:08.730 --> 00:12:11.190
The hunt's on. my beastbros!

170
00:12:23.030 --> 00:12:24.580
No one fucks with the Animals!

171
00:12:24.660 --> 00:12:27.200
- Suckers...
- Mom! Brake! Brake hard!

172
00:12:27.290 --> 00:12:28.790
Watch out!

173
00:12:40.090 --> 00:12:42.600
Mom? Mom!

174
00:12:50.390 --> 00:12:53.400
Is that the Trauma Team? Oh. thank Christ.

175
00:12:55.270 --> 00:12:57.650
He's not a client.

176
00:12:57.740 --> 00:12:59.200
Neither is she.

177
00:12:59.280 --> 00:13:00.280
Hey. wait!

178
00:13:00.320 --> 00:13:03.910
Secure the policyholder.
Leave them to the city meat wagons.

179
00:13:03.990 --> 00:13:05.700
- Copy that.
- What?

180
00:13:05.780 --> 00:13:08.450
What the hell? Hey! Where are you going?

181
00:13:09.410 --> 00:13:10.710
Shit!

182
00:13:10.790 --> 00:13:12.710
No way. Just gonna leave us here?

183
00:13:12.790 --> 00:13:15.710
Mom! Momma!

184
00:13:15.790 --> 00:13:17.710
Mom. wake up!

185
00:13:17.800 --> 00:13:19.720
Fucking piece of...

186
00:13:19.800 --> 00:13:24.260
Mom! Dammit. get off me!

187
00:13:24.350 --> 00:13:27.970
- Shit. Get the fuck off!
- Dammit!

188
00:13:28.060 --> 00:13:31.020
Mom!

189
00:13:31.100 --> 00:13:32.480
Fuck!

190
00:13:36.440 --> 00:13:38.070
Surgery was a success.

191
00:13:38.150 --> 00:13:41.200
Your mother hasn't come to just yet.
but she's stable.

192
00:13:41.280 --> 00:13:43.410
Need her to stay a few more nights.

193
00:13:43.490 --> 00:13:45.780
Oh. Then. is it okay if I see her?

194
00:13:45.870 --> 00:13:49.540
No can do. buddy.
Visitation ain't part of your package.

195
00:13:49.620 --> 00:13:51.040
Oh. Right.

196
00:13:51.120 --> 00:13:54.000
Anyway. I should get started
on the paperwork.

197
00:13:54.080 --> 00:13:55.500
Brought your mom's things.

198
00:13:55.580 --> 00:13:58.460
And don't forget to zip us those eds.
Got three days.

199
00:13:58.550 --> 00:14:00.050
- Uh...
- Yeah.

200
00:14:00.130 --> 00:14:01.530
There's a reason everyone
in Night City

201
00:14:01.550 --> 00:14:03.130
wants insurance.

202
00:14:03.220 --> 00:14:04.220
Stay safe now.

203
00:14:04.970 --> 00:14:07.470
Yeah. hoop ship. Version back.

204
00:14:08.260 --> 00:14:10.770
Is that all? You low-balling me? Huh?

205
00:14:11.560 --> 00:14:13.770
Nah. forget it. choom.

206
00:14:14.440 --> 00:14:16.360
Dammit! Hmm?

207
00:14:18.940 --> 00:14:20.610
What the fuck?

208
00:14:22.110 --> 00:14:23.740
<i>♪ I ain't your average sicko ♪</i>

209
00:14:23.820 --> 00:14:25.490
<i>♪ I'm dead. just like disco ♪</i>

210
00:14:25.570 --> 00:14:28.030
<i>♪ My bank account
Is zero-zero-zero. oh no ♪</i>

211
00:14:28.120 --> 00:14:29.990
Another account. Christ.

212
00:14:30.080 --> 00:14:33.540
Just enough. She saved so much.
Never knew.

213
00:14:34.250 --> 00:14:36.540
So. that. it settled the medical.

214
00:14:38.750 --> 00:14:41.510
Still gotta cover rent. Huh?

215
00:14:42.130 --> 00:14:45.760
Doc? Hey. you get the still I sent?
Listen.

216
00:14:45.840 --> 00:14:50.010
Don't think I'd forgotten I owe you a kick
in the nuts for that shoddy bootleg.

217
00:14:50.100 --> 00:14:51.600
But check this.

218
00:14:52.220 --> 00:14:53.350
Cyberware.

219
00:14:53.980 --> 00:14:57.810
Yeah. looks. uh. military. doesn't it?

220
00:14:57.900 --> 00:14:59.520
How do you think it would fetch

221
00:14:59.610 --> 00:15:02.480
if I was interested
and the price was right?

222
00:15:03.280 --> 00:15:05.110
Not selling. Just want an estimate.

223
00:15:08.070 --> 00:15:10.910
Nah. fuck that noise.
No way it's that cheap.

224
00:15:13.910 --> 00:15:15.920
Oh. come on. choom.

225
00:15:18.000 --> 00:15:20.040
Whatev! Wasn't selling anyways.

226
00:15:20.130 --> 00:15:23.880
By the way. Don't expect me
to push your XBDs at school anymore!

227
00:15:25.670 --> 00:15:28.430
Any pinchin' hack had taken me for a gonk.

228
00:15:29.510 --> 00:15:31.600
A Sandevistan.

229
00:15:31.680 --> 00:15:36.100
No serial number and what?
Military-grade. this thing. really?

230
00:15:36.190 --> 00:15:39.150
It definitely ain't legal. But whatev.

231
00:15:39.230 --> 00:15:41.650
Whoa! The hell are these specs?

232
00:15:54.910 --> 00:15:56.580
Huh? Ah!

233
00:16:02.000 --> 00:16:04.460
Little piece of advice. Martinez.

234
00:16:04.550 --> 00:16:07.380
- Learn to take a hint.
- About what?

235
00:16:07.470 --> 00:16:10.300
Our class.
You're not welcome. Got it?

236
00:16:10.390 --> 00:16:11.990
Huh? If this is about yesterday...

237
00:16:12.010 --> 00:16:14.220
- Who said anything about yesterday?
- What?

238
00:16:14.310 --> 00:16:17.890
You probably figure I give you a hard time
'cause you're poor. Simply untrue.

239
00:16:17.980 --> 00:16:19.980
I'm rather charitably inclined.

240
00:16:20.060 --> 00:16:22.480
Not your fault you were born
on the wrong side of society.

241
00:16:22.560 --> 00:16:25.360
There's no rule
that says a street kid

242
00:16:25.440 --> 00:16:26.920
can't make it at the Academy.

243
00:16:26.940 --> 00:16:28.610
provided they pay their way.

244
00:16:28.700 --> 00:16:31.450
What cracks my chrome
is something else entirely.

245
00:16:31.530 --> 00:16:32.870
- Know what?
- Look. choom.

246
00:16:32.950 --> 00:16:35.350
I haven't understood
a single thing coming out of your mouth.

247
00:16:35.370 --> 00:16:36.700
- That right there!
- Hmm...

248
00:16:36.790 --> 00:16:39.460
Time to get gone.
Just drop out. why don't ya?

249
00:16:39.540 --> 00:16:41.670
- Huh?
- You're a misfit. an anomaly.

250
00:16:41.750 --> 00:16:44.960
Human but trash. and there's nothing
that can change that.

251
00:16:45.050 --> 00:16:48.340
Rot in you runs as deep
as your bones. Martinez.

252
00:16:48.420 --> 00:16:51.840
Best you can do
is not spread it to the rest of us.

253
00:16:51.930 --> 00:16:53.470
Did I just short-circ?

254
00:16:53.550 --> 00:16:56.430
Said you didn't care
as long as I paid tuition.

255
00:16:56.520 --> 00:16:58.930
I heard your mommy came in
to see the principal.

256
00:16:59.020 --> 00:17:01.230
ask forgiveness for your little stunt.

257
00:17:01.310 --> 00:17:02.520
Caused quite a scene.

258
00:17:02.600 --> 00:17:05.570
crying for her baby boy.
begging for him not to get expelled.

259
00:17:05.650 --> 00:17:06.860
So shameless.

260
00:17:06.940 --> 00:17:09.650
You know. since we're chatting.
I've just always wondered.

261
00:17:09.740 --> 00:17:13.120
How could she afford to send you
to Arasaka Academy anyway?

262
00:17:13.200 --> 00:17:16.120
Care to explain. Martinez?

263
00:17:16.700 --> 00:17:20.370
Go on. Tell us.
How does Mommy pay your way?

264
00:17:20.460 --> 00:17:22.750
What's any Night City bottomfeeder

265
00:17:22.830 --> 00:17:24.880
do to make a quick eurobuck. huh?

266
00:17:24.960 --> 00:17:28.510
Oh! A couple of pretty
salacious things come to mind.

267
00:17:28.590 --> 00:17:29.670
Tired of this shit.

268
00:17:29.720 --> 00:17:32.630
- Hold on. choom. Who said we were done?
- Fuck off!

269
00:17:42.930 --> 00:17:45.270
Oh? What?

270
00:17:53.070 --> 00:17:56.490
Got anything slotted?
Anime freeware maybe?

271
00:18:21.730 --> 00:18:23.060
I knew it.

272
00:18:23.140 --> 00:18:28.020
Nothing like the Strongarms 400 to bring
out the best in your kung-fu chipware.

273
00:18:28.110 --> 00:18:30.400
Organic knuckles? Seriously?

274
00:18:30.480 --> 00:18:34.030
Wanna try me again?
I suggest you pack some serious chrome.

275
00:18:34.110 --> 00:18:35.950
Or just drop out.

276
00:18:36.030 --> 00:18:38.530
You know what I'd prefer.

277
00:18:43.960 --> 00:18:46.580
<i>Mr. Martinez?</i>

278
00:18:47.420 --> 00:18:51.170
<i>I'm calling in regards
to Gloria Martinez's condition.</i>

279
00:18:51.840 --> 00:18:54.220
- Huh?
- She was stable this morning.

280
00:18:54.300 --> 00:18:57.680
but then her vitals began to nosedive
really out of nowhere.

281
00:18:57.760 --> 00:19:02.560
But you said the surgery was successful.

282
00:19:02.640 --> 00:19:05.980
True. But only so much
we can do on the discount package.

283
00:19:06.060 --> 00:19:09.150
Worn down as she was.
I doubt she'd had lasted much longer.

284
00:19:09.230 --> 00:19:11.190
Overworked. seemed to me.

285
00:19:11.280 --> 00:19:14.440
Anyway. I'm supposed to tell you
we offer some burial options.

286
00:19:14.530 --> 00:19:17.820
People in Night City
want corpo gigs for a reason. kid.

287
00:19:18.620 --> 00:19:21.830
<i>Greetings. valued
customer. We are sorry for your loss.</i>

288
00:19:21.910 --> 00:19:23.870
<i>To ease things at this difficult time.</i>

289
00:19:23.950 --> 00:19:26.040
<i>we can deliver the body
of your dearly departed</i>

290
00:19:26.120 --> 00:19:28.210
<i>to your home or to a funeral home.</i>

291
00:19:28.290 --> 00:19:29.460
<i>Would you like to learn more?</i>

292
00:19:29.540 --> 00:19:31.090
I got a choice?

293
00:19:31.170 --> 00:19:33.760
<i>Is our budget-friendly
cremation service right for you?</i>

294
00:19:33.840 --> 00:19:37.930
<i>Waive those pesky delivery fees
and bring your loved one home today.</i>

295
00:19:46.020 --> 00:19:47.180
<i>Don't walk.</i>

296
00:19:47.230 --> 00:19:48.960
<i>- Good day. Mrs. Martinez.
- Don't walk.</i>

297
00:19:48.980 --> 00:19:50.540
<i>- We've received a quote for the repairs
- Don't walk.</i>

298
00:19:50.560 --> 00:19:52.170
<i>- to our system infrastructure.
- Don't walk.</i>

299
00:19:52.190 --> 00:19:55.610
<i>As agreed. I've sent you an e-mail
with the payment details.</i>

300
00:19:55.690 --> 00:19:57.450
<i>Also. perhaps you've had time to think?</i>

301
00:19:57.530 --> 00:19:58.740
<i>Do let me know.</i>

302
00:19:58.820 --> 00:20:00.880
<i>Just say the word
and we'll begin making arrangements</i>

303
00:20:00.910 --> 00:20:03.290
<i>for David's transfer
to another institution.</i>

304
00:20:03.370 --> 00:20:05.760
<i>Please note.
To maintain your utilities contract.</i>

305
00:20:05.790 --> 00:20:08.460
<i>you must pay a penalty of 500 euro-dollars</i>

306
00:20:08.540 --> 00:20:12.340
<i>in addition to any past
due amounts and late fees.</i>

307
00:20:12.420 --> 00:20:14.340
<i>If you cannot pay by the deadline.</i>

308
00:20:14.420 --> 00:20:17.930
<i>your services will be terminated
in the following order...</i>

309
00:20:18.010 --> 00:20:20.680
<i>Trauma Team.
Clear a path immediately.</i>

310
00:20:20.760 --> 00:20:22.860
<i>- ...medical...
- Ding-ding. Martinez!</i>

311
00:20:22.890 --> 00:20:24.890
<i>Me again. Time's up.</i>

312
00:20:24.970 --> 00:20:27.180
<i>Rent's long past due.</i>

313
00:20:27.270 --> 00:20:29.850
<i>Keep this shit up
and I won't just change your lock.</i>

314
00:20:29.940 --> 00:20:32.940
<i>I'll throw your ass out
on the street. You feel me?</i>

315
00:20:33.020 --> 00:20:35.190
<i>♪ City burn ♪</i>

316
00:20:35.280 --> 00:20:40.360
<i>♪ We're not planning to return ♪</i>

317
00:20:40.450 --> 00:20:43.700
<i>♪ Trying so hard to be free ♪</i>

318
00:20:49.290 --> 00:20:52.750
The implant I showed you.
you said you'd take it off me for 10K?

319
00:20:53.840 --> 00:20:56.210
Six now? Said ten yesterday. choom!

320
00:20:56.300 --> 00:20:58.340
Come on. That's just one fucking day.

321
00:20:58.420 --> 00:21:00.590
And we both know that it's worth way more!

322
00:21:00.680 --> 00:21:02.840
Hell yeah. I looked into it. and I...

323
00:21:05.430 --> 00:21:08.520
Oh. yeah? Well. fuck you too! Bitch.

324
00:21:14.310 --> 00:21:17.320
<i>Katsuo here. I heard about your mom.</i>

325
00:21:17.400 --> 00:21:21.070
<i>I could offer my sympathies.
but find it hard to sympathize.</i>

326
00:21:21.150 --> 00:21:23.240
<i>God only knows what she had to endure</i>

327
00:21:23.320 --> 00:21:26.240
<i>to send her delinquent son to an Academy
he doesn't belong at.</i>

328
00:21:26.990 --> 00:21:29.410
<i>Her methods couldn't have been noble</i>

329
00:21:29.500 --> 00:21:33.540
<i>if she died in a car accident. So mundane.</i>

330
00:21:33.630 --> 00:21:34.670
<i>But you know?</i>

331
00:21:34.750 --> 00:21:37.750
<i>Karma. There's a lesson in this. David.</i>

332
00:21:39.090 --> 00:21:41.930
<i>Your mother tried to live
beyond her means and died.</i>

333
00:21:42.680 --> 00:21:44.010
<i>Don't make the same mistake.</i>

334
00:22:00.570 --> 00:22:02.610
Christ. The hell. Who is that?

335
00:22:03.280 --> 00:22:05.620
David. hey.

336
00:22:06.950 --> 00:22:08.740
That the big bad Sandy?

337
00:22:08.830 --> 00:22:12.330
Not a badge or fixer in town
who's not looking for that beauty.

338
00:22:12.410 --> 00:22:14.120
I told you though...

339
00:22:14.210 --> 00:22:18.050
ain't gonna find anyone
that's willing to take it off your hands.

340
00:22:18.130 --> 00:22:20.630
I'm not here to sell.

341
00:22:20.710 --> 00:22:25.140
I want this fused here.
'Bout time I chrome the fuck up.

342
00:22:44.180 --> 00:22:50.060
Eyes burning a way to me

343
00:22:50.770 --> 00:22:56.060
Eyes destroying so sweetly

344
00:22:57.150 --> 00:23:02.860
Now there is a fire in me

345
00:23:02.860 --> 00:23:11.120
A fire that burns

346
00:23:36.900 --> 00:23:39.560
This fire is out of control

347
00:23:39.560 --> 00:23:42.230
I'll burn. I'll burn. I'll burn

348
00:23:42.230 --> 00:23:43.780
I'll burn it down

349
00:23:53.040 --> 00:23:55.500
I'll burn. I'll burn. I'll burn

350
00:23:55.500 --> 00:23:57.080
I'll burn it down
